## Phase 1: Markdown Parsing Implementation

### Create Markdown Parser Module
- [ ] Create new file `src/processing/markdown_parser.py` (must be <250 lines)
- [ ] Implement `extract_image_url(markdown_content: str) -> str` function
  - Use regex pattern `r'!\[.*?\]\((https?://[^\)]+)\)'` to find first image
  - Raise ValueError with message "No image URL found in markdown" if not found
  - Add type hints and docstring
  - Keep function under 15 lines
  - **PRD Reference**: Section 05.1, 06.2
  
- [ ] Implement `extract_prompt_text(markdown_content: str) -> str` function
  - Use regex pattern `r'```[a-zA-Z]*\n(.*?)\n```'` with re.DOTALL flag
  - Extract content from first code block (any language identifier or none)
  - Strip leading/trailing whitespace from extracted content
  - Raise ValueError "No code block found in markdown" if not found
  - Raise ValueError "Empty code block in markdown" if content is empty after stripping
  - Add type hints and docstring
  - Keep function under 20 lines
  - **PRD Reference**: Section 05.1, 06.2

- [ ] Add unit docstring examples in markdown_parser.py showing usage with example1.md format
  - **PRD Reference**: Section 07.2

