## Phase 3: Payload Construction Updates

### Create Image Input Array Builder
- [ ] Add function `build_image_input_array(markdown_url: str, profile_url: str = None) -> list` to markdown_parser.py
  - If profile_url exists: return [markdown_url, profile_url]
  - If profile_url is None or empty string: return [markdown_url]
  - Always return list/array, never single string
  - Add type hints and docstring
  - Keep function under 10 lines
  - **PRD Reference**: Section 06.2

### Update Processor for Image URL Extraction
- [ ] Modify `src/processing/processor.py` to extract image URLs from markdown files
  - Import extract_image_url from markdown_parser
  - Read markdown file content in processing loop
  - Extract image URL using extract_image_url(content)
  - Store extracted URL for payload construction
  - **PRD Reference**: Section 05.2

- [ ] Update payload construction in processor.py to build image_input array
  - Call build_image_input_array(markdown_url, profile.get('image_input'))
  - Set payload['image_input'] to the returned array (not 'parameters.image_input')
  - Ensure image_input is always array format, never single string
  - **PRD Reference**: Section 05.2

- [ ] Update prompt construction to apply prefix/suffix from profile
  - Get prompt_prefix from profile (default to empty string)
  - Get prompt_suffix from profile (default to empty string)
  - Construct final prompt: f"{prefix}{markdown_text}{suffix}"
  - Strip any double spaces from concatenation
  - **PRD Reference**: Section 05.2

